r la surface de la terre; d\'en exposer le syst\xc3\xa8me g\xc3\xa9n\xc3\xa9ral aux hommes avec qui nous vivons, &amp; de le transmettre aux hommes qui viendront apr\xc3\xa8s nous; afin que les travaux des siecles pass\xc3\xa9s n\'aient pas \xc3\xa9t\xc3\xa9 des travaux inutiles pour les siecles qui succ\xc3\xa9deront; que nos neveux, devenant plus instruits, deviennent en m\xc3\xaame tems plus vertueux &amp; plus heureux, &amp; que nous ne mourions pas sans avoir bien m\xc3\xa9rit\xc3\xa9 du genre humain.\' Accessed from <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://artflsrv02.uchicago.edu/cgi-bin/philologic/getobject.pl?c.4:1252.encyclopedie0513">http://artflsrv02.uchicago.edu/cgi-bin/philologic/getobject.pl?c.4:1252.encyclopedie0513</a>.</span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<dl>\n<dt>Sources</dt>\n</dl>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Philipp_Blom" title="Philipp Blom">Blom, Philipp</a>, <i>Enlightening the world: Encyclop\xc3\xa9die, the book that changed the course of history</i>, New York: Palgrave Macmillan, 2005, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-4039-6895-0" title="Special:BookSources/1-4039-6895-0">1-4039-6895-0</a></li>\n<li>Brewer, Daniel. <i>The Discourse of Enlightenment in Eighteenth-century France: Diderot and the Art of Philosophizing</i>. Cambridge, England: Cambridge UP, 1993.</li>\n<li>Brewer, Daniel, "The <i>Encyclop\xc3\xa9die</i>: Innovation and Legacy" in <i>New Essays on Diderot</i>, edited by James Fowler, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2011, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-521-76956-6" title="Special:BookSources/0-521-76956-6">0-521-76956-6</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Peter_Burke_(historian)" title="Peter Burke (historian)">Burke, Peter</a>, <i>A social history of knowledge: from Gutenberg to Diderot</i>, Malden: Blackwell Publi